                            <comment id="17190325" author="beobal" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2020 17:31:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks to be due to the fact that a task submitted to an executor may not immediately begin execution even if capacity exists to do so. Repro&apos;s reliably when run in Docker with restricted cpu and adding a spin assert with a short timeout seems to fix it. It&apos;s probably of little value, but I&apos;ve linked a Circle run with the medium config as in the original report.&lt;/p&gt;

